Sentencas: A multi-physics model is developed to investigate the thermal stresses in a micro-tubular SOFC, based on a previously developed thermal-fluids model predicting cell operation.
Titulo: Thermal stresses in an operating micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Mechanical properties of the anode and cathode are determined theoretically through composite structure approximation.
Titulo: Thermal stresses in an operating micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Residual stresses arisen during the fabrication of the cell due to the mismatch in thermal expansion coefficients are calculated by accounting for each fabrication process separately.
Titulo: Thermal stresses in an operating micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The interactions between the cell, the sealant and the alumina tube are accounted for a better representation of the actual fuel cell test setup.
Titulo: Thermal stresses in an operating micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effect of sealant and alumina tube on the stress distribution in the cell is investigated and it is found out that near the fuel cell-sealant interface stress distribution changes significantly.
Titulo: Thermal stresses in an operating micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effect of spatial temperature gradient on the stress distribution is also analyzed and found to have a minimal impact for a typical fuel cell operation at mid-range current densities.
Titulo: Thermal stresses in an operating micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effects of oxygen vacancies caused by the reduction of the GDC electrolyte on the overall stress distribution are also shown.
Titulo: Thermal stresses in an operating micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Oxygen vacancies of the electrolyte result in relaxation of the stresses due to the alleviation of mismatch in Young's modulus between different layers of the cell.
Titulo: Thermal stresses in an operating micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell
